<HEADLINE>
FT  22 APR 94 / International Company News: Arbitration fails to resolve
McCain dispute
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By BERNARD SIMON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TORONTO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
An arbitrator has failed to resolve the three-year succession dispute
between Harrison and Wallace McCain, the brothers who control McCain Foods,
the multinational frozen-foods group based in the Canadian province of New
Brunswick.
Though the mediator declared invalid a resolution passed by the McCain board
which sought to remove Mr Wallace McCain as joint chief executive, he made
no finding on the brothers' disagreement over who should succeed them. Mr
Wallace McCain favours his son Michael, while
Mr Harrison McCain prefers Mr Allison McCain, who holds a senior position in
the group's UK subsidiary.
</TEXT>
