FT  22 APR 94 / Campaign Diary: Tebbit turns on party colleagues
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROLAND RUDD
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Lord Tebbit, the former Conservative party chairman, took the unprecedented
step of using the leftwing Tribune magazine to criticise government and
opposition 'machine politicians' who want a European single currency.
The leading opponent of the Maastricht treaty on European union overshadowed
his own party's attempts to set its agenda in the local and European
elections with an attack on federalists in all parties.
He said: 'Politics today makes for strange bedfellows. We liberals of the
right stand alongside socialists such as Tony Benn, conviction politicians
all.
'While machine politicians huddle together in an irreconcilable conflict of
interests between their responsibilities to the sovereign people and
parliament of this nation and their obligation to the European Union.'
A cabinet minister said Lord Tebbit should 'know better than attack his own
party during an election campaign'. He described Lord Tebbit's article 'as
dangerous nonsense'.
