<HEADLINE>
FT  22 APR 94 / Council tax rules to be changed
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The government is to alter rules that threatened thousands of householders
with backdated demands for higher council tax.
Increasing activity in the housing market has uncovered mistakes in valuing
homes for council-tax purposes, leading to demands for the higher tax
backdated to April 1993.
Changes to the council tax regulations announced last night mean that the
higher tax will apply only from the date of revaluation. However, where the
value of a property is decreased, the householder will still be able to
claim back the extra tax paid since April 1993.
