<HEADLINE>
FT  22 APR 94 / Union rejects coal package
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Members of the Union of Democratic Mineworkers have rejected by 2,121 to 177
an offer by British Coal to pay each miner Pounds 6,000 as part of a package
including changes in working patterns.
The package, which British Coal said would not be improved, would introduce
compulsory weekend work and 12-hour shifts. It would also provide redundancy
payments of up to Pounds 27,000 from April 30 compared with an existing
maximum of more than Pounds 45,000.
