FT  22 APR 94 / Council tax rules changed
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The government is to alter rules that threatened thousands of householders
with backdated demands for higher council tax.
Increasing activity in the housing market has uncovered mistakes in valuing
homes for council tax purposes which led to demands for the higher tax
backdated to April 1993. Changes to the council tax regulations announced
last night mean that the higher tax will apply only from the date of
revaluation.
