FT  22 APR 94 / India may sell train inspection
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW DELHI
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Indian railways, one of the largest rail networks in the world, is
considering handing over its massive ticket control system to private
agencies, according to Mr MK Rao, the Railway Board chairman, Reuter reports
from New Delhi.
He said the move would help cut losses incurred as a result of people
travelling without tickets. Private agencies would be expected to be more
diligent in examining tickets, he said. Officials were 'seriously thinking
of handing over ticket examination work to private agencies to increase
income'.
