FT  22 APR 94 / Sihanouk defies threat from Khmer Rouge
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AP
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   PHNOM PENH
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
King Norodom Sihanouk said the Khmer Rouge yesterday urged him to leave
Cambodia at once because the guerrillas plan 'big trouble in Phnom Penh and
throughout Cambodia', AP reports from Phnom Penh.
King Sihanouk said the letter from Mr Khieu Samphan, the Khmer Rouge
president, said 'his troops will conduct big trouble, starting from
tomorrow'. The king said he would not leave.
Khmer Rouge attacks have escalated in recent days. On Tuesday the Khmer
Rouge recaptured its headquarters at Pailin, in western Cambodia near the
Thai border.
