FT  21 APR 94 / International Company News: TNT debt rating upgraded by S&amp;P
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NIKKI TAIT
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Standard &amp; Poor's, the US credit rating agency, yesterday upgraded its
senior debt rating for TNT, the Australian transportation group, from B to
B+, writes Nikki Tait.
S&amp;P, which had indicated such a move was being considered, said that 'as a
result of management's financial restructuring, the overall debt burden was
now more manageable, with improving discretionary cashflow and liquid
balances expected to meet debt maturities'. It made the move after TNT
completed a USDollars 100m senior debt offering.
TNT, which has been bedevilled by a heavy debt burden and boardroom upheaval
last year, has also raised funds by a converting preference share issue and
the sale of various 'non-core' assets.
