<HEADLINE>
FT  21 APR 94 / International Company News: Comalco warns of bleak outlook
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NIKKI TAIT
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Comalco, the Australian integrated aluminium producer in which CRA holds a
majority interest, said yesterday that it broke even in the first quarter of
1994, with a January loss followed by profits in February and March, writes
Nikki Tait.
However, Comalco's chairman, Mr John Ralph, warned shareholders that the
immediate outlook for the aluminium industry was bleak, with oversupply and
high inventories continuing.
Most of Comalco's business, he said, was 'still operating in difficult
market conditions'. The medium to longer-term outlook was more positive, 'as
fundamental demand remains strong with sound growth expected in end-uses
such as automobiles and packaging, and increased per capita consumption in
Asia'.
Mr Ralph later added that the company was considering equity-raising
possibilities, but that no decisions had been taken. 'We are looking at all
funding alternatives and that includes the possibility of equity,' he said.
