</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LAURIE MORSE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Dean Witter Discover, the US brokerage firm spun off as an independent
company last year by the retailer Sears, Roebuck, reported record
first-quarter earnings of Dollars 209.5m, or Dollars 1.23 a share.
That was an increase of 54 per cent on last year's first-quarter earnings of
Dollars 136.4m, or per share income, on a pro-forma basis, of 80 cents.
First-quarter operating revenues were Dollars 1.27bn, up 17 per cent from
Dollars 1.08bn.
Dean Witter's Discover Card credit card operations outperformed its
securities business. The credit card division saw operating revenues rise 33
per cent to Dollars 542.4m, from Dollars 408.7m in last year's first
quarter.
Net operating revenues for Dean Witter's securities business edged up 8 per
cent in the first quarter, to Dollars 727.7m, from Dollars 672.9m a year
ago.
The company said that the assets it managed in its securities business grew
14 per cent in the quarter, to Dollars 70.9bn, and that managed loans
increased 15 per cent, to Dollars 20.5bn.
The company added 2.4m new Discover Card accounts in the quarter, bringing
the total to 29.6m.
In its securities business, Dean Witter added 536 account executives in the
first quarter, bringing its total sales force to 7,701 brokers.
