<HEADLINE>
FT  21 APR 94 / UK Company News: Havelock Europa stages recovery with Pounds
2.28m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JAMES BUXTON, Scottish Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Havelock Europa, the store-fitting company, yesterday met expectations with
a turnround from losses of Pounds 3.07m to profits of Pounds 2.28m pre-tax
for 1993.
Turnover was up 7 per cent at Pounds 35.3m (Pounds 32.9m).
The improvement was attributed to measures taken to reduce the cost base and
raise productivity following the 1992 financial restructuring, as well as to
stronger demand as the economy recovers.
Net cash at the year end was Pounds 2.5m, compared with net debt of Pounds
2.2m.
The company, which last paid a dividend in 1991, is proposing a final of 2p,
payable from earnings of 8.4p (losses 15.4p) per share.
Mr Norman Lessels, chairman, said the payment was a good foundation on which
to base a progressive dividend policy, and reflected the fact that the
company would eventually be subject to a full tax charge.
Havelock, which operates from plants in Dalgety Bay, near Edinburgh, and in
Nottingham, designs, builds and installs commercial interiors. Most of its
turnover comes from retailers, led by Boots and Marks and Spencer, with
further work for Woolworths, Burton and House of Fraser.
It is, however, doing increasing work for the financial services sector
which accounted for 17 per cent of turnover in 1993, against 12 per cent in
1992. 'This will be the major area for our growth,' Mr Hew Balfour, chief
executive, said.
Havelock serves institutions such as National Westminster Bank and the
Co-operative Bank. In 1994 it has installed pre-fabricated installations for
First National Bank of Southern Africa in Johannesburg and for Yapikredit in
Istanbul. On both it worked with AT&amp;T Global Solutions, formerly NCR, which
supplied self-service banking equipment.
Mr Lessels said the order book was substantially ahead of last year's,
though there was marked resistance to price increases in traditional
business.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Companies:-
</XX>
<CO>Havelock Europa.
</CO>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>GBZ  United Kingdom, EC.
</CN>
<XX>
